<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="397" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1692,2042]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1411,153,460]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="397" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,315,1982,2006]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
By the wing pattern, the new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bucsek, 2012" authorityName="Bucsek" authorityYear="2012" box="[846,1203,1982,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Halone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dissimulata">
<emphasis box="[846,1053,1982,2006]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Halone dissimulata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bucsek, K." box="[1059,1203,1982,2006]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" refId="ref3326" refString="Bucsek, K. (2012) Erebidae, Arctiinae (Lithosiini, Arctiini) of Malay Peninsula - Malaysia. Institute of Zoology SAS, Bratislava, 170 pp." type="book" year="2012">Bucsek, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bucsek, K." box="[1217,1360,1982,2006]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" refId="ref3326" refString="Bucsek, K. (2012) Erebidae, Arctiinae (Lithosiini, Arctiini) of Malay Peninsula - Malaysia. Institute of Zoology SAS, Bratislava, 170 pp." type="book" year="2012">Bucsek 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 85, pl. 15: 213, 213a, 213b, 213c, gen. Mal091, 126; present paper: fig. 23), but the new species can be distinguished from the latter by the forewing with a pale brown basal band; medial discal area with two dark short streaks (discoidal and post˗discal); hindwing gray (
<figureCitation box="[319,446,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1839,1863]" captionTargetBox="[157,1404,460,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[157,1407,471,1812]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults of Halone spp. from Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam. 1a. H. ariadna, male, Cambodia (INU˗1009C). 1b. ditto, male, Vietnam (INU˗10040V). 1c. ditto, male, Laos (INU˗10045L). 1d. ditto, female, Laos (INU˗10073L). 2a. H. hollowayi n. sp., male, Cambodia (paratype, INU˗1568C). 2b. ditto, female, Cambodia (holotype, INU˗10033C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644444/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">Figs. 2a, 2b</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bucsek" authorityYear="2012" box="[495,648,189,213]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Halone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dissimulata">
<emphasis box="[495,648,189,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">H. dissimulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, forewing without a pale brown basal band; medial discal area with two dark, rounded spots (discoidal and post˗discal); hindwing light gray (
<bibRefCitation author="Bucsek, K." box="[872,1014,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" refId="ref3326" refString="Bucsek, K. (2012) Erebidae, Arctiinae (Lithosiini, Arctiini) of Malay Peninsula - Malaysia. Institute of Zoology SAS, Bratislava, 170 pp." type="book" year="2012">Bucsek 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 85, pl. 15: 213, 213a, 213b, 213c).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1411,153,460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">
The male genitalia of the new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bucsek, 2014" authorityName="Bucsek" authorityYear="2014" box="[764,1037,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Halone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viktorai">
<emphasis box="[764,881,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">H. viktorai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bucsek, K." box="[891,1037,259,283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="397" refId="ref3357" refString="Bucsek, K. (2014) Erebidae, Arctiinae (Lithosiini, Arctiini) of Malay Peninsula - Malaysia. Supplementum. Institute of Zoology SAS, Bratislava, 42 pp." type="book" year="2014">Bucsek, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bucsek, K." pageId="2" pageNumber="397" refId="ref3357" refString="Bucsek, K. (2014) Erebidae, Arctiinae (Lithosiini, Arctiini) of Malay Peninsula - Malaysia. Supplementum. Institute of Zoology SAS, Bratislava, 42 pp." type="book" year="2014">Bucsek 2014: 17, pl. 3: 31, gen. MalS25</bibRefCitation>
), but the new species can be distinguished from the latter by the projections of tegumen tapering, weakly curled; valva stout, with blunt, rectangular apex, 0.5 times shorter than projections of tegumen; saccular process more stout, with blunt, rectangular apex, 0.5 times shorter than projections of tegumen (
<figureCitation box="[892,956,365,389]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–6" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[254,1361,165,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1423,165,1800]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–6. Genitalia of Halone spp. 3. H. ariadna, male, Cambodia (INU˗1009C). 4. ditto, female, Laos (INU˗10072L). 5. H. hollowayi n. sp., male (paratype, INU˗1568C). 6. ditto, female (holotype, INU˗10033C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644446/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="397">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). In 
