<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="399" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,154,718]" pageId="4" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,154,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="399">Description</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[337,395,154,178]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="399">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[409,537,154,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1839,1863]" captionTargetBox="[157,1404,460,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[157,1407,471,1812]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults of Halone spp. from Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam. 1a. H. ariadna, male, Cambodia (INU˗1009C). 1b. ditto, male, Vietnam (INU˗10040V). 1c. ditto, male, Laos (INU˗10045L). 1d. ditto, female, Laos (INU˗10073L). 2a. H. hollowayi n. sp., male, Cambodia (paratype, INU˗1568C). 2b. ditto, female, Cambodia (holotype, INU˗10033C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644444/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="399">Figs. 2a, 2b</figureCitation>
). Length of the forewing 
<quantity box="[808,891,154,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="399" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7˗9 mm</quantity>
in both sexes. Head sordid white. Patagium, tegula and thorax sordid white, with pale brown sprinkles. Forewing ground color sordid white, with a basal band narrow, pale brown; medial band broad, slightly rounded (waved), pale brown, diffused from a dark, short discoidal streak (= antemedial streak) to dorsum, with dark inner edge; post˗discal short streak dark; postmedial line pale brown, slender, broadly curved; subterminal line pale brown, slender, zigzag; series of small terminal spots pale brown; cilia pale gray. Hindwing gray, with a pale costal area; cilia gray. Abdomen fuscous in male; pale gray, tinged with pale yellow in female. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="399">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[263,329,370,394]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–6" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[254,1361,165,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1423,165,1800]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–6. Genitalia of Halone spp. 3. H. ariadna, male, Cambodia (INU˗1009C). 4. ditto, female, Laos (INU˗10072L). 5. H. hollowayi n. sp., male (paratype, INU˗1568C). 6. ditto, female (holotype, INU˗10033C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644446/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="399">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Uncus stout, club˗shaped, with an angular apex. Tegumen rectangular, sclerotized, shouldered, with a pair, weakly coiled slender projections. Valva elongated rectangular, weakly sclerotized, apex blunt, heavily covered with setae, almost same length with uncus. Apical saccular process elongated rectangular, strongly sclerotized, apex dilated rectangular, heavily covered with setae, almost same length with valva. Juxta weakly sclerotized. Saccus broadly “U”˗shaped. Aedeagus waved in apical half, with a large spine˗shaped apical projection and vesica with a large, elongate, spine˗shaped cornutus and scobinated. 
<emphasis box="[569,751,550,574]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="399">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[765,831,550,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–6" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1902,1924]" captionTargetBox="[254,1361,165,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1423,165,1800]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–6. Genitalia of Halone spp. 3. H. ariadna, male, Cambodia (INU˗1009C). 4. ditto, female, Laos (INU˗10072L). 5. H. hollowayi n. sp., male (paratype, INU˗1568C). 6. ditto, female (holotype, INU˗10033C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644446/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="399">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales weakly covered with setae. Ostial plate sclerotized, with dentated margin. Ductus bursae short, tubular, weakly sclerotized. Corpus bursae globular, membranous, with a slender, crescent˗shaped signum in cervix of bursae and a bundle of diverse sized spines in medial area of bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
